Sylvester Gilbert Whiton, a general insurance broker, decorated veteran of the first World War, prominent Mason and Episcopal layman, died of a heart attack on Sunday at his home, 689 East Nineteenth Street, Brooklyn. Mr. Whiton's office was at 111 Fulton Street. His age was 50. View Full Article in Timesmachine Â»
